      net.minestom.server.codec.Codec.RegistryTaggedUnion(Registries.Selector<StructCodec<? extends T>>, Function<T, StructCodec<? extends T>>, String)
      Use Codec.RegistryTaggedUnion(String, Registries.Selector, Function) instead. Creates a StructCodec to bidirectionally map values of T to their encoded values
      Registry selectors will be used to lookup values of codecs of T. Then will be used to map to object T from key
      net.minestom.server.codec.Codec.RegistryTaggedUnion(Registry<StructCodec<? extends T>>, Function<T, StructCodec<? extends T>>, String)
      Use Codec.RegistryTaggedUnion(String, Registry, Function) instead. Shortcut for Codec.RegistryTaggedUnion(Registries.Selector, Function, String)
